{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584848","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584848"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:58:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:58:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14820"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14820","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14820"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7511"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58835"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7511","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7511"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14820"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44242"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"7643"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18363"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/58835"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring mitosis, chromosomes undergo a series of coordinated movements to ensure equal distribution of genetic material to daughter cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the events of anaphase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chromosomes align at the cell equator","Sister chromatids replicate","Nuclear envelope breaks down","Chromatin begins to condense","Sister chromatids separate and move to opposite poles"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring anaphase, \u003Cstrong\u003Esister chromatids separate and move to opposite poles\u003C/strong\u003E of the cell through two main mechanisms. First, kinetochore microtubules shorten through depolymerisation, pulling the chromatids apart. Second, polar microtubules elongate, pushing the spindle poles further apart.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChromosome alignment at the cell equator\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during metaphase. \u003Cstrong\u003ENuclear envelope breakdown\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Echromatin condensation\u003C/strong\u003E are events of prophase. \u003Cstrong\u003ESister chromatid replication\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during S phase of interphase, not during mitosis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe separation of sister chromatids during anaphase requires the enzyme separase to cleave cohesin proteins that hold sister chromatids together. This process is carefully regulated to ensure accurate chromosome segregation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["During anaphase, sister chromatids separate and move to opposite poles of the cell.","Kinetochore microtubules shorten to pull chromatids apart while polar microtubules elongate to push poles apart.","Cohesin proteins must be cleaved to allow sister chromatid separation."],"references":["Alberts B, Bray D, Johnson A, Lewis J, Raff M, Roberts K, et al. Cell communities: tissues, stem cells, and cancer. Essential cell biology, 4th New York Edition: Garland Science; 2018.","Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44242"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14820"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44242","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44242"},"a